        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p>You cause plants in the area to entangle your foes, with the effects of Entangle (see below).</p>\n<p>A creature that critically fails the save takes [[/r 2d4 #persistent bleed]] @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Persistent Damage]{Persistent Bleed Damage} in addition to being @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Immobilized]{Immobilized}.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Escape]{Escaping} your bramble doesn't end the bleed damage.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (+1)</strong> The bleed damage on a critical failure increases by [[/r 1d4 #persistent bleed]].</p>\n<hr />\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: 500;\">@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Entangle]{Entangle}</span></h4>\n<p>Plants in the area entangle creatures. The area counts as difficult terrain. Each round that a creature starts its turn in the area, it must attempt a Reflex save.</p>\n<p>On a failure, it takes a -10-foot circumstance penalty to its Speeds until it leaves the area, and on a critical failure, it is also @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Immobilized]{Immobilized} for 1 round.</p>\n<p>Creatures can attempt to Escape at entangle's DC to remove these effects.</p>"
        },
